{"data":{"actions":[{"callId":"chatcmpl-tool-9fc07e547b1840e4","input":{"filename":"access-request-approver-prioritized-report.md","title":"Access Request Approver – Prioritized Action Report","markdown":"# Access Request Approver – Prioritized Action Report (≤ 500 words)\n\n**Evidence**\n- Dossier loaded (agent ID: 31‑access‑request‑approver).\n- Records analyzed via `analyze_records` (top 3 items, risk/opportunity scores provided).\n\n**Assumptions**\n- The three retrieved records represent the current actionable workload for the Access Request Approver.\n- No additional unseen high‑risk items exist beyond the returned set (reasonable given the analysis limit of 10).\n- Actions recommended will be implemented by the security team or appropriate stakeholder, subject to approval for any grant of privileges.\n\n**Prioritization Logic**\n1. **Risk score** (higher = more urgent) weighted against **impact** (business value of the request).\n2. **Status** influences immediacy: `urgent` > `in_review` > `blocked`.\n3. **Opportunity score** (potential improvement) considered secondary to risk mitigation.\n\n**Top Priorities**\n| Rank | Record ID | Title | Risk | Impact | Status | Recommended Action |\n|------|-----------|-------|------|--------|--------|--------------------|\n| 1 | **31‑A** | Access request approver priority case | **9** (high) | 51,827 | urgent | • Review request details immediately.\\n• Verify least‑privilege compliance.\\n• If compliant, prepare approval; if not, request clarification or propose alternative minimal access. |\n| 2 | **31‑C** | Access request approver blocked follow‑up | **10** (critical) but **blocked** | 24,541 | blocked | • Identify the external dependency causing the block.\\n• Coordinate with the responsible team to unblock.\\n• Once cleared, apply the same risk‑impact review as Record 31‑A. |\n| 3 | **31‑B** | Access request approver routine queue item | **4** (moderate) | 12,503 | in_review | • Perform standard least‑privilege check.\\n• Approve or reject based on policy.\\n• Document decision for audit trail. |\n\n**Action Summary**\n1. **Immediate** – Resolve Record 31‑A; it carries the highest combined risk and impact. Allocate an analyst to complete the review within the next 4 hours.\n2. **Unblocking** – For Record 31‑C, open a cross‑team ticket to clarify the blocker. Set a 1‑day SLA for resolution; treat the pending work as high priority once unblocked.\n3. **Routine** – Process Record 31‑B in parallel after the urgent item, ensuring the standard checklist (policy reference, justification, audit log) is followed.\n\n**Next Steps & Monitoring**\n- Update the access‑request dashboard with status changes.\n- Log all approvals/rejections with references to the least‑privilege policy.\n- Conduct a brief post‑action review to capture any policy gaps revealed by the urgent case.\n\n*Prepared by the Access Request Approver agent (ID: 31‑access‑request‑approver).*\n"},"kind":"tool-call","toolName":"write_report"}],"sequence":0,"stepIndex":3,"turnId":"turn_0"},"type":"actions.requested","meta":{"at":"2026-06-18T15:19:56.023Z"}}
